==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Caffeine
<hw>Caf*fe"ine</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>caf⟦eacute⟧ine</ets>. See
<er>Coffee</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white, bitter,
crystallizable substance, found in coffee and tea. It is identical with
the <isa>alkaloid</isa> <altname>theine</altname> from tea leaves, and
with <altname>guaranine</altname> from guarana. It is responsible for
most of the stimulating effect of coffee or tea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caffetannic</ent>⟦br⟧
